[{"question":"When you heard Todd Akin\u0027s comments, what was your reaction?","answer":"Well, both that what he said was actually inaccurate and also very dangerous.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":46,"aSentId":47},{"question":"ORGAN: How would you have felt if you had been compelled to have that baby by the rapist who raped you?","answer":"Well, that is the key point.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":60,"aSentId":61},{"question":"Isn\u0027t that what a modern America should stand for?","answer":"You know, modern America has said, according to the Supreme Court, that it is cruel and unusual punishment to give the death penalty for rapists.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":114,"aSentId":115},{"question":"Why should that woman who feels that strongly the other way to you not have the same right that you did?","answer":"You know, I may not look the same as I did when I was 4 years old or 4 weeks old unborn in my mother\u0027s womb.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":144,"aSentId":145},{"question":"Well, what good is my right to anything as a woman if I don\u0027t have my right to life?","answer":"Well, let me just tell you, there -- you brought up people in a coma.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":181,"aSentId":182},{"question":"And what does it mean for the presidential battle?","answer":"Well, obviously, what he said is despicable and outrageous, and it\u0027s good at least to see his own party trying to banish him from the race.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":315,"aSentId":316},{"question":"What is the core of the problem for America incorporated, when you look at it, do you think?","answer":"You know, Piers, what we\u0027ve really argued in this book is we didn\u0027t get here by accident.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":334,"aSentId":335},{"question":"I mean, what -- when you look at the Ryan Budget Plan, Romney\u0027s amendment of that, you look at what President Obama is saying, what do you think is the most sensible way forward for America to finance all this?","answer":"You know, there\u0027s no question to me that we have to agree on one thing, that the only way to deal with the budget deficit that big is with both tax revenue and spending cuts.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":355,"aSentId":356},{"question":"Tom, when you hear Romney talking tough on Iran, and we\u0027ve also got the Syria situation bubbling away as well, do you think that the Romney/Ryan ticket has enough foreign policy experience to know what to do about these two crises?","answer":"I think they have an incredibly weak foreign policy biography between the two of them and a rather weak team, frankly.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":379,"aSentId":380},{"question":"And why shouldn\u0027t they assume it will be coming their way?","answer":"Well, you know, it\u0027s a very legitimate question.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":389,"aSentId":390},{"question":"Isn\u0027t it time that somebody did something?","answer":"The problem with Syria is that unlike other Arab awakening revolutions -- you know, Libya imploded.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":413,"aSentId":414},{"question":"How are you?","answer":"I\u0027m well.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":459,"aSentId":460},{"question":"Yourself?","answer":"Here\u0027s the thing, I\u0027m a Christian, you\u0027re a Christian.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":461,"aSentId":462},{"question":"Do you feel that being Christian has become almost a bad word in a country that\u0027s still predominantly Christian?","answer":"We have a branding problem probably.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":465,"aSentId":466},{"question":"Has he lived up to the expectation, hopes that you had?","answer":"Well, here\u0027s the -- I mean, I always avoided politics, especially as a comedian because you\u0027re alienating half the thing.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":507,"aSentId":508},{"question":"For you, Romney is the more likely of the candidates?","answer":"He\u0027s a successful businessman.","docId":"120821pmt","qSentId":524,"aSentId":525}]